# A Log-likelihoods
## A. 1 OIPP model

From equation 7, the log-likelihood for the one-inflated positive Poisson (OIPP) model is:

$$
\begin{aligned}
\ell= & \sum_{i=1}^{n}\left\{\log \left(1-\omega_{i}\right)+I_{1} \log \left[\frac{\omega_{i}}{1-\omega_{i}}+\frac{\lambda_{i}}{\exp \lambda_{i}-1}\right]\right. \\
& \left.+\left(1-I_{1}\right)\left[y_{i} \log \lambda_{i}-\log \left[\exp \lambda_{i}-1\right]-\log y_{i}!\right]\right\}
\end{aligned}
$$

where $I_{1}=1$ if $y_{i}=1$ and 0 otherwise, and where $\lambda_{i}$ and $\omega_{i}$ have been previously defined.
